 for the price","detail":"It connects one of Jeju''s strongest UNESCO landmarks with heritage, living culture, and a signature beach without the price jump of a private format."},{"label":"The route does not feel one-note","detail":"Cave atmosphere, village heritage, summit scenery, haenyeo culture, and beach time each give the day a clearly different mood."},{"label":"The finish gets easier, not harder","detail":"After the active Seongsan segment, the haenyeo stop and Hamdeok finish help the day land more comfortably."}]},{"title":"How the walking load actually feels","icon":"footprints","iconBg":"bg-amber-50/80","iconColor":"text-amber-600","items":[{"label":"Mostly manageable, with one clearly demanding stop","detail":"Ilchul Land, Seongeup, the haenyeo stop, and Hamdeok are manageable for most travelers, while Seongsan Ilchulbong is the one stop that adds real stairs and incline."},{"label":"More active than a pure panorama bus route","detail":"The route stays within normal day-tour range, but it is not a purely passive coach sightseeing day because of Seongsan."},{"label":"Mixed-age groups can usually handle it","detail":"The route works for many mixed-age groups as long as they are comfortable either climbing Seongsan or using the lower-area option."}]},{"title":"When weather changes on site","icon":"cloud-rain","iconBg":"bg-slate-50/80","iconColor":"text-slate-600","items":[{"label":"The route is more resilient than a fully exposed east-coast plan","detail":"Ilchul Land gives useful indoor-outdoor flexibility at the start, and the Jeju Haenyeo Museum is a clean cultural fallback if the live show is cancelled."},{"label":"Seongsan and Hamdeok remain weather-sensitive","detail":"Wind, rain, and visibility changes most strongly affect the UNESCO climb and beach finish."},{"label":"Operational substitutions should preserve the story","detail":"If weather forces a change, the best adjustment is not random replacement but keeping the East Jeju culture-and-coast logic intact."}]}]},"practicalAccordionItems":[{"id":"pickup","title":"Pickup and Return Times","preview":"4 fixed pickup points + 5 city drop-off points","content":["Pickup: 08:30 Ocean Suites Hotel","Pickup: 08:45 Jeju Airport, 3rd Floor Gate 3","Pickup: 08:55 Lotte City Hotel Jeju","Pickup: 09:05 Shilla Duty Free Shop","Drop-off: Ocean Suites Hotel","Drop-off: Jeju Airport, 3rd Floor Gate 3","Drop-off: Lotte City Hotel Jeju","Drop-off: Shilla Duty Free Shop","Extra drop-off available at Dongmun Market","Expected return to Jeju City around 17:40–18:20 depending on traffic, weather, and show operation","Please arrive at least 10 minutes early at your selected pickup point"]},{"id":"walking","title":"Walking and Terrain","preview":"Moderate overall, with Seongsan as the key active stop","content":["Ilchul Land, Seongeup Folk Village, the haenyeo stop, and Hamdeok are generally manageable for most travelers","Seongsan Ilchulbong is the most physically demanding stop because of stairs and uphill sections","If needed, some travelers can limit themselves to the lower area at Seongsan instead of pushing to the summit","Comfortable walking shoes with grip are strongly recommended"]},{"id":"weather","title":"Weather and Route Adjustments","preview":"Most affected by wind at Seongsan, the haenyeo stop, and Hamdeok","content":["Light rain: the tour usually still operates","Heavy rain, rough sea, or strong wind: the haenyeo show may be cancelled and replaced with Jeju Haenyeo Museum","Seongsan Ilchulbong summit access and comfort level can be affected by weather and crowd conditions","If a stop becomes unsafe or impractical, timing or stop order may be adjusted while preserving the East Jeju route logic"]},{"id":"wear","title":"What to Wear and Bring","preview":"Walking shoes, layers, and wind protection are the basics","content":["Comfortable walking shoes with good grip","A light jacket or windproof outer layer","Sun protection and a hat on clear days","Water bottle","A small 